08/01/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The government reportedly has intensified preparations for starting an operation to collect illegal weapons from the public. The newspaper <I>Dnevnik</I> reported Wednesday (8 January) that the operation would likely start in the middle of the year, after the government establishes a national committee to co-ordinate the process and adopts new legislation on arms possession. The entire operation is expected to last 18 months. According to unofficial data, the population owns some 600,000 weapons. (Dnevnik - 08/01/03; A1 TV - 07/01/03; MIA - 06/01/03)
